Notes: 1 = Not affected  ; 2 = Spent more than half of the monthly income ; 3 = Spent all the monthly income ; 4 = Spent savings or borrowed ; 5 = Forced to sell household goods

ElementDescription: How much trouble did your family or relatives have because of depression?
Notes: 1 = None ; 2 = Mild, some family members changed their daily routine. ; 3 = Moderately, some family members missed work or regular activities. They were emotionally affected ; 4 = Severe, the family members had to make important changes and they left work. ; 5 = Overwhelming, many family members had to make important changes. They were very affected.
